  <documentation>Group of Atoms for use in Assignment. Connects Resonance and Atom records. All Atoms connected to an AtomSet are by definition equivalent and in fast exchange throughout the project. Atoms in an atomSet could be e.g. the protons of any -CH3 or -NH3 group, or HD1/HD2 in a fast-flipping Phe, or free water protons with either bound water protons (molecular exchange) or Ser OH protons (proton exchange). Atoms that can not be in an AtomSet are e.g. a Lys epsilon CH2 (not in fast exchange) or Phe HD1/HD2 if the Phe is in slow exchange under any circumstances within the project.</documentation>
